title: For Sale:  Norinco Model 213 (M213)
postcontent: For sale is a Norinco M213 with a front sight blade painted with a white dot, aftermarket grips. Slide stop has been replaced with a new Tokarev slide stop.The Model 213 is a civilian 9mm variant of the Type 54, which itself is a copy of the iconic Tokarev. The Type 54 has been called "The Black Star." The Model 213 has a magwell spacer in it which may be removed, allowing you to use Type 54 magazines.If you replace the barrel and the bushing and remove the spacer, you will be able to fire Tok ammunition. If you change the slide and do the above, it is a total conversion to a Type 54 setup. The 9mm slide's ejection port is too short to cycle unfired Tok ammo, meaning that it is not recommended to carry it with Tok ammo and the 213 slide due to the possibility of a jam being unable to be conventionally cleared.This means that if you buy a Tok ammo slide, barrel and bushing, remove the magwell, and use Tok ammo magazines you will have a pistol which you can convert to 9mm by only replacing the barrel and bushing and then pushing 9mm ammo to the front of the Tok ammo magazines while loading.Kept as-is, it is a reliable and shockingly accurate, especially for its price, pistol with some interesting history.Includes one magazine with a pinky shelf and one magazine's worth of ball ammunition in addition to the original box.A great gun for a collector, beginner, or as a backup for a ready kit.

title: For Sale:  Deal Alert! Sig Sauer P290RS with Night Sights, new with ammo and extras!
location: Lake Worth, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
Do you want a top-tier concealed carry platform for an unbeatable price? Are you a fan of revolvers but want faster reloads and better concealability? Do you want safety, compactness and versatility without sacrificing accuracy? Are you a first time shooter or an experienced pistoleer looking for your next trusty pocket monster?
If you answered "yes" to any of those questions, you might want to keep reading. If none of those hypoteticals applied to you, you've come this far already- keep reading.The P290RS is the sturdy BMW of pocket rockets. Chambered in 9mm, the "RS" stands for re-strike, meaning the pistol has the ability to allow you a second chance at a misfired round/pistol pushed out of battery before executing remedial action! Not that you'll need it of course, this thing was built to keep shooting under even the most extreme conditions.The A-10 Warthog of pocket pistols, the P290RS understands what a man (or woman) wants when they truly appreciate the art of the gun. Built like a tank with Sig Sauer quality in a package rivaling the Glock 43-sized competition, the 290RS stands apart in safety, reliability and most importantly, accuracy.
Having fired many rounds from the 290RS series (not this specific pistol, of course- it has only had the test fire for reliability done), you are going to be *amazed* at how accurate the 290RS is. Despite having a trigger feel akin to a tuned carry revolver (which makes it perfect for people who like a good revolver but want faster reloads, better accuracy and more capacity), the 290RS is a smooth shooter that has effortless follow-up, excellent safety features and a clean pull. She's user friendly, for newbies and experienced pistoleers alike.Of course, this isn't all the 290RS package has to offer. With tritium night sights, the 290RS literally requires *nothing* to be considered "carry ready"- this baby is ready to fly right outside of the box. Speaking of the box, everything that came from the factory is included in the box- SIG decal, manual, warranty card, takedown tools, 7-round and 8-round magazines, Lucas Gun Oil, safety lock and an open-carry holster (which you could technically wear under a shirt in Florida until a dedicated IWB holster comes your way).
In the spirit of being a good host, I'm including a safety orange snap cap (for safe dry fire training) and a box of ammunition. Basically, your first trip to the range is (kinda) on me, just pay your own range fee.
So, at this point, I'm guessing all this sounds too good to be true. Don't sweat it. I just got married on July 4, so I have to slim my collection down a bit. Deciding between the 290RS and another sidearm came down to a coin toss. That said, I'm not desperate for cash, so don't think about low-balling. So here is what you're getting:
P290RS with night sights
x1 7rd flush magazinex1 8rd extended magazinex1 casedocuments, lubrication, takedown toolsx1 snap capx1 box of ammunitionx1 holsterMust have Florida state ID or CCW. CCW holders preferred, though any and everyone interested will sign a hand reciept stating that you can A) legally own the firearm and B) have no intention of using the firearm for illicit activities. I reserve the right to refuse sale to anyone.Make my loss your gain and take home a concealed carry/self-defense powerhouse at a fraction of the price today!

A small-scale interpretation of the completely adjustable VP grip feature — consisting of interchangeable backstraps and lateral grip panels — is replicated in the compact grip frame of the VP9SK. This allows the pistol to be easily modified to fit any individual user and is a feature found only on Heckler & Koch handguns. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. The VPSK has the features of the latest, state-of-the-art handgun. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame and the paddle style magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters. HK’s patented charging supports, found on full size VP pistols, are also present on the VPSK. The charging supports are simple components that are mounted on each side of the rear of the slide and provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide rearward. The charging supports speed reloading and make operating the VP easier for shooters with reduced hand strength. VPSK pistols can use a variety of proven HK magazines, including compact double stack 10-round and 13-round with either flat or extended floorplates for a more ergonomic grip. The VPSK can also use the same high capacity 15-round magazine used by the full size VP and P30 handguns. Magazine sleeves that replicate the grip profile of the VP handgun are also available. VPSK pistols have an abbreviated Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into their polymer frame for mounting lights and accessories. VPSK pistols use a proprietary captive flat recoil spring that helps reduce the recoil forces affecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component life span. HK’s famous cold hammer forged barrel — made from cannon grade steel — ensures a long service life. Similar HK barrels on 9 mm P30 models have fired more than 90,000 rounds in endurance tests in 2010. The polygonal bore profile, with no traditional lands-and-grooves rifling, contributes to longer service life as well as a slight increase in muzzle velocity. The VPSK’s machined steel slide is protected from corrosion and wear by HK’s hostile environment finish and all metal components, including springs and pins have superior metallurgy. Despite their small size, VPSK subcompacts have excellent weight and balance making them naturally pointable, easy to control, and accurate to shoot. VPSK models are currently available in 9 mm. VPSK pistols are made in Heckler & Koch’s Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany and are well suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use.
